					"numinlets" : 1,
					"numoutlets" : 0,
					"patching_rect" : [ 14.0, 80.0, 658.0, 108.0 ],
					"text" : "This cross-synthesis implementation uses an older MSP technique based on overlapping fft~/ifft~ pairs and explicit windowing to achieve frequency-domain signal processing.. (Compare with pfft~) Each of the two input signals, signal A and B, are converted to a corresponding frequency-domain signal using the fft~ object. Signal A is then convolved (complex multiplied) with the amplitude spectrum of signal B. The resulting output signal will retain some, or most of the original frequency content of signal A, while its energy (or spectral envelope) will be largely determined by signal B's energy. The output depends on the spectral intersection of both signals, so crossing whale grunts with piccolo harmonics will result in silence.",
					"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
				}

